
This directory contains the example configurations for the different ways Cassandra cluster can bset up. 

nodes.pp.2     		: Cassandra Cluster with Vcider Virtual Network (http://www.vcider.com/)
nodes.pp.3     		: Cassandra Cluster Setup With Amazon EC2 Multi Region Setup. No internode encryption. Uses EC2Snitch. 
nodes.pp.4     	 	: Cassandra Cluster Setup With Amazon EC2 Multi Region Setup. Internode encryption enabled. Uses EC2Snitch.
nodes.openvpn.pp.1  	: Cassandra Cluster Setup With Amazon EC2 Multi Region Setup. No internode encryption. Uses EC2Snitch. 
			  Uses OpenVPN for nodes <=> client communcation.  
nodes.openvpn.pp.1      : Cassandra Cluster Setup With Amazon EC2 Multi Region Setup. No internode encryption. Uses EC2Snitch.
                          Uses OpenVPN for nodes <=> client communcation. 

By default nodes.pp is a copy of nodes.pp.2. 

To configure your Cassandra Cluster, 
 - Choose Appropriate Configuration Set Above
 - Update the configurations in the file. e.g IP Addres, Seed Host etc. 
 - Copy the file as nodes.pp 
     e.g. cp nodes.pp.4 nodes.pp
 - Puppet will automatically pick up nodes.pp 

